</section>
<section id="fs-idm377705376" class="section-summary">
<title>Summary of Learning Outcomes</title>
<list id="fs-idm384974192" list-type="enumerated" start-value="4">
<item>How does the Federal Deposit Insurance Corporation (FDIC) protect depositors’ funds?</item>
</list>
<para id="fs-idm387653488">The Federal Deposit Insurance Corporation insures deposits in commercial banks through the Bank Insurance Fund and deposits in thrift institutions through the Savings Association Insurance Fund. Deposits in credit unions are insured by the National Credit Union Share Insurance Fund, which is administered by the National Credit Union Administration. The FDIC sets banking policies and practices and reviews banks annually to ensure that they operate fairly and profitably.</para>
</section>
