<definition id="fs-idm384924720"><term>Federal Deposit Insurance Corporation (FDIC)</term>
<meaning id="fs-idm373796352">An independent, quasi-public corporation backed by the full faith and credit of the U.S. government that insures deposits in commercial banks and thrift institutions for up to a ceiling of $250,000 per account.</meaning>
</definition>
